    <!--Parameter for about activity-->
    <string name="about_app_description_part_one">
        <large><b>Description of the app:</b></large>
        \n\n<small>The App FloriBot HMI was build at Heilbronn University within a Bachelor thesis.
        With this app you can control a robot in two axes, like the robot FloriBot of Heilbronn University with a differential drive.
        If you tilt the phone then the robot will drive in x - direction (translation). If you turn the phone (like a steering wheel)
        then you can turn the robot around z - axis.
        </small>
    </string>

     <string name="about_app_description_part_two">
         \n\n<small>The operation system of the robot is the <i>Robot Operating System</i> (ROS).
         In general you can send and receive data on existing topics.
         To do so, the app creates a publisher to provide control data on a specific topic.
         With the created subscriber the verification data (send from the robot) were received.
        </small>
    </string>

    <string name="about_app_functions">
        <large><b>Possibilities of the app:</b></large>
        \n\n<small>You can control the robot in two operation modes. The manual and the automatic mode.
        In the manual mode you can decide between control with the acceleration sensor and simple joystick buttons.
        If you want to control the robot with joystick buttons you can adjust the current acceleration value with a slider bar.
        To visualize the acceleration quantity there are two progress bars. One for the translation in x - axis and the other
        for the steering around the z - axis.
        \nThese visualization is only present in manual mode with sensor control.
        </small>
    </string>

